    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="Marketplace Fees and ATLAS Locking" class="article-title">
          Marketplace Fees and ATLAS Locking
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2025-12-08T18:23:09Z" title="2025-12-08T18:23:09Z" data-datetime="relative">December 08, 2025 18:23</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/47061466167827-Marketplace-Fees-and-ATLAS-Locking/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><h3 id="h_01KBJM3RMPYEP09FDQBXBFRXXY">Why Do I Pay a ~0.00203 SOL Fee When Buying Items?</h3><p>When you buy a ship or resource for the first time, you might notice a small <strong>Solana network fee (~0.00203 SOL)</strong>. This happens because:</p><ul>
<li><p>On <strong>Solana</strong>, each token type (e.g., ATLAS, ships, food, fuel) needs its <strong>own Token Account</strong></p></li>
<li><p>Creating this account requires a small deposit of SOL to make it <strong>rent-exempt</strong></p></li>
</ul><p>💡 Example:<br>If you buy <strong>AMMO, FUEL, FOOD, and TOOLS</strong> for the first time, you’ll pay the SOL fee for each resource. These are <strong>one-time fees per token type, </strong>not per transaction.</p><h3 id="h_01KBJM4DE989Y4RQ3XCZEP3MPE">Can I Get My SOL Deposit Back?</h3><p>Yes. If you decide to stop playing, you can <strong>close these Token Accounts</strong> and reclaim your SOL using:</p><ul>
<li><p><a href="https://sonar.watch/" target="_new" rel="noopener">Sonar Watch</a></p></li>
<li><p><a href="https://app.step.finance/" target="_new" rel="noopener">Step Finance</a></p></li>
</ul><p>However:</p><ul><li><p>If you close an account and later want to <strong>buy that item again</strong>, you'll need to <strong>pay the fee again</strong> to reopen the Token Account</p></li></ul><h3 id="h_01KBJM4DE9QBWCHKVHVPRQAE3B">Marketplace Transaction Fees</h3><p>When someone <strong>sells an item</strong> on the Star Atlas Marketplace:</p><ul>
<li><p>A <strong>6% fee</strong> is charged (the <strong>buyer pays nothing</strong>).</p></li>
<li>
<p>The fee is split:</p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong>2%</strong> to the DAO Treasury (1/3 of fee)</p></li>
<li><p><strong>4%</strong> to ATMTA (2/3 of fee)</p></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul><p>This fee can be <strong>reduced by locking ATLAS</strong></p><h3 id="h_01KBJM4DE9CBJN7N4BXZWPJVEH">ATLAS Locker &amp; Marketplace Discounts</h3><p>You can lock ATLAS tokens in the <strong>ATLAS Locker</strong> to <strong>earn daily POLIS rewards</strong> and <strong>reduce Marketplace fees</strong>.</p><div><div>
<p><img class="wysiwyg-image-resized hs-image-align-none" style="aspect-ratio: 688/239; height: auto; width: 688px;" src="https://20489070.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/20489070/undefined-Sep-01-2022-03-25-28-54-PM.png" width="688" height="239"></p>
<div><div></div></div>
</div></div><p>Example:<br>With 560,000 ATLAS locked, you only pay <strong>4.5%</strong> in Marketplace fees instead of 6%.</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

